File: Health workers fill out documents before performing tests for COVID-19 coronavirus on other health workers at the screening and testing tents set up at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Johannesburg, on April 15, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Forty-six more people have died of COVID-19 in South Africa. This brings the country's death total to 1,877. The total number of confirmed cases is now at 92,681, which is an increase of 4,966. The country has recorded over 50,000 recoveries. More than 1.2-million tests have been conducted.